      • al_get_clipboard_text

        public static com.sun.jna.Pointer al_get_clipboard_text(AllegroLibrary.ALLEGRO_DISPLAY display)
        al_get_clipboard_text returns the text on the clipboard. Allegro has called al_malloc(long) on this string, and expects you to call al_free(Pointer) on it. That is why the binding can not return String, as it would copy the string and leak memory. Use jalleg_get_clipboard_text(ALLEGRO_DISPLAY) to copy to a String and free the native memory.

      • jalleg_get_clipboard_text

        public static java.lang.String jalleg_get_clipboard_text(AllegroLibrary.ALLEGRO_DISPLAY display)
        Makes a direct call to al_get_clipboard_text(ALLEGRO_DISPLAY) and transforms the results into a Java String without a memory leak.
